@startuml Task Status State Diagram
' Workflow test - updated
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam roundcorner 10

title Task Status State Machine

state "Not Started" as NotStarted
state "In Progress" as InProgress
state "On Hold" as OnHold
state "Completed" as Completed
state "Cancelled" as Cancelled

[*] --> NotStarted : Task created

NotStarted --> InProgress : Start task
InProgress --> OnHold : Pause task
OnHold --> InProgress : Resume task
InProgress --> Completed : Complete task
InProgress --> Cancelled : Cancel task
OnHold --> Cancelled : Cancel task
NotStarted --> Cancelled : Cancel task

Completed --> [*] : Task finished
Cancelled --> [*] : Task removed

note right of NotStarted
  **Initial State:**
  - Task created
  - Not yet started
  - Can be assigned
end note

note right of InProgress
  **Active State:**
  - Task in work
  - Can be paused
  - Can be completed
end note

note right of OnHold
  **Paused State:**
  - Task temporarily stopped
  - Can be resumed
  - Can be cancelled
end note

note right of Completed
  **Final State:**
  - Task finished
  - completed_date set
  - Cannot be changed
end note

note right of Cancelled
  **Final State:**
  - Task cancelled
  - Cannot be resumed
  - Cannot be completed
end note

@enduml

